{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/timeoutaddsecondsfull(priority:interval:function:data:notify:)"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets a function to be called at regular intervals, with "},{"code":"priority","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"timeoutAddSecondsFull","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"priority"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"interval","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"function"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"GSourceFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFunc"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"notify"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"GDestroyNotify","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GDestroyNotify"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The function is called repeatedly until it returns [const","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceRemove","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"],"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"at which point the timeout is automatically destroyed and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the function will not be called again.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike [func"},{"code":"GLib.timeout_add","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"], this function operates at whole second"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"granularity. The initial starting point of the timer is determined by the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"implementation and the implementation is expected to group multiple timers","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"together so that they fire all at the same time. To allow this grouping,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"interval"},{"text":" to the first timer is rounded and can deviate up to one second","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from the specified interval. Subsequent timer iterations will generally run"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"at the specified interval."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that timeout functions may be delayed, due to the processing of other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"event sources. Thus they should not be relied on for precise timing.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"After each call to the timeout function, the time of the next","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"timeout is recalculated based on the current time and the given "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"interval"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"main-loop.html#memory-management-of-sources","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for details"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on how to handle the return value and memory management of "},{"code":"data","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want timing more precise than whole seconds, use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.timeout_add","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] instead."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The grouping of timers to fire at the same time results in a more power","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and CPU efficient behavior so if your timer is in multiples of seconds","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and you don’t require the first timer exactly one second from now, the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"use of [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.timeout_add_seconds"},{"type":"text","text":"] is preferred over"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.timeout_add"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This internally creates a main loop source using"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.timeout_source_new_seconds"},{"type":"text","text":"] and attaches it to the main loop"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"context using [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.Source.attach","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]. You can do these steps manually","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"if you need greater control.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It is safe to call this function from any thread.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The interval given is in terms of monotonic time, not wall clock"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time. See [func"},{"code":"GLib.get_monotonic_time","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GL